@Node "M21_OPCAT" "ImagedeskE.guide/M21_OPCAT"
@Next "M21_GNCAT"
@Toc "M2_PROJ"

Open Catalog
............

   This menu item branches in two subitems:

   @{b}*@{ub}     @{b}Selectable@{ub} - opens a requester in which a former generated
     catalog file has to be choosen. If this file could not be
     identified as a catalog file, you will get an error message. In
     the other case, a window is opened, giving information about free
     space for thumbnail objects on the desk and the number of entries
     in the catalog file. The window contains two slider gadgets where
     the first entry to load and the number of thumbnail objects to
     load could be specified. Existing thumbnail objects on the desk
     won't be replaced, therefore it is sometimes neccessary to remove
     all of them from the desk with @{b}Clean Desk First@{ub} before new ones are
     loaded. Loading is started when the @{b}Load@{ub}-button has been pressed.
     A process monitor will show approximately the current state of the
     loading procedure. It could be interrupted by pressing the ESC-key.

   @{b}*@{ub}     @{b}Quick@{ub} - the selection window won't be opend. The catalog file
     is loaded immediately. There will be just as many thumbnails
     loaded as there will fit on the screen.


@EndNode

@Node "M21_GNCAT" "ImagedeskE.guide/M21_GNCAT"
@Next "M21_RSING"
@Prev "M21_OPCAT"
@Toc "M2_PROJ"

Generate Catalog
................

   This menu item branches in two subitems:

   @{b}*@{ub}     @{b}Show Thumbnails@{ub} - First of all a filename is requested for the
     catalogfile to be generated. After this another requester opens
     where path and a template for the picture files could be choosen.
     An additional selected file will be ignored. If the @{b}OK@{ub}-button has
     been pressed, ImageDesk starts to examine all files listed in the
     requester for being a supported format. In this case, a thumbnail
     object will be generated which occurs as an intuition gadget on
     the screen.

     @{i}Caution:@{ui} If there is no space left on the desk for a single
     thumbnail image, all existing objects will be removed from the
     desk without any demand.  However, this will not influence the
     file which is generated.

     The process monitor which occurs during the generation process
     helps by estimating the current state of the procedure. To stop
     the thumbnail generation, press the ESC-key and it will be
     interrupted on the next possible point of time.

     @{i}Remark:@{ui} If the generation process has been interrupted, all former
     generated objects will be saved correctly.

   @{b}*@{ub}     @{b}Don't show Thumbnails@{ub} - Acts exactly like @{b}Show Thumbnails@{ub}, but
     the generated thumbnail images won't occur on the desk.


@EndNode

