@Node "M1_BUGRP" "ImagedeskE.guide/M1_BUGRP"
@Next "M1_FUTUR"
@Prev "M1_RIGHT"
@Toc "Main"

Known Bugs
**********

   The following bugs are known:

   @{b}*@{ub} Some of the image decoding functions are not very tolerant of
     corrupt image files.  This could cause system crashes.

   @{b}*@{ub} If `MagicMenu' has been installed some menu colors will be
     displayed wrongly.


@EndNode

@Node "M1_FUTUR" "ImagedeskE.guide/M1_FUTUR"
@Next "M1_HISTO"
@Prev "M1_BUGRP"
@Toc "Main"

Future
******

   The following list should give a reference which features future
releases of ImageDesk may have. The succession of this list does not
say anything, at all.

   @{b}*@{ub} AREXX Port

   @{b}*@{ub} Better error handling of corrupt image files

   @{b}*@{ub} Asynchronous window management

   @{b}*@{ub} Speed improvements for the dog slow GIF and IFF decoders

   @{b}*@{ub} Decrease of the memory usage during thumbnail generations runs

   @{b}*@{ub} Support for further image formats

   @{b}*@{ub} Add a Toolbar


@EndNode

@Node "M1_HISTO" "ImagedeskE.guide/M1_HISTO"
@Next "M1_THANX"
@Prev "M1_FUTUR"
@Toc "Main"

Releases
********

0.97 Beta
---------

   First beta release.

0.98 Beta
---------

   @{b}*@{ub} Now the default publicscreen ist left to the workbench as long as
     it is not neccessary for ImageDesk to declare its screen to the
     default publicscreen.

   @{b}*@{ub} Before closing the screen, ImageDesk now checks if other
     applications have opened their windows on ImageDesk's publicscreen.

   @{b}*@{ub} Don't try to load IFF-ILBM images with unknown compression type
     anymore.

   @{b}*@{ub} Filenames for the external viewers may contain spaces, yet.

   @{b}*@{ub} The slidergadgets in the @{b}Load Catalog@{ub} control window are now
     managed correctly.

   @{b}*@{ub} A few catalog file tools have been added (@{b}CATList@{ub}, @{b}CATChPath@{ub},
     @{b}CATRepack@{ub}, @{b}CATJoin@{ub} and @{b}CATRemEntry@{ub}).

1.0 - first public release
--------------------------

   @{b}*@{ub} Added internal window viewer.

   @{b}*@{ub} Removed small bug in the BMP reader.

   @{b}*@{ub} System font will be opened correct, now.

   @{b}*@{ub} Added dither option for 8-bit displays.

1.01
----

   @{b}*@{ub} Fixed bug: Village Screenmode requester sometime has been opened
     on the workbench screen.

   @{b}*@{ub} Fixed bug in the JPEG Picasso viewer: 8-bit JPEGs where displayed
     wrongly on the 8-bit screens.

   @{b}*@{ub} Fixed a wrong palette entry in the 8-bit Picasso viewer.

   @{b}*@{ub} Improved display speed of the window viewer for truecolor images.

1.02
----

   @{b}*@{ub} Added Scrollbars to the window viewer.

1.1
---

   @{b}*@{ub} Added Switch `Use Original Palette' for the window viewers.

   @{b}*@{ub} Now supports and generates project icons for catalogs.

1.11
----

   @{b}*@{ub} Thumbnail generation from 4-bit BMPs reported an error - Fixed.

   @{b}*@{ub} Now The name of the screen is displayed instead of the ID in the
     System Prefs window.

1.12
----

   @{b}*@{ub} 'Default Public Screen' has not been set back to workbench if the
     Picasso screenrequester has been used - Fixed.

1.2
---

   @{b}*@{ub} Fixed bug: If no complete path has been specified for a catalog
     file to be generated, some problems could have been arised while
     saving.

   @{b}*@{ub} CyberGraphics and standard 8 bit intuition screens are supported.

   @{b}*@{ub} The state of @{i}Show Image Infos@{ui} is stored in the prefs file.

   @{b}*@{ub} The information window now shows the current graphics board mode.

   @{b}*@{ub} Added new menu item @{i}Ask Before Cleaning Desk@{ui}.

   @{b}*@{ub}     @{i}Open Catalog@{ui} now branches into subitems: @{i}Selectable@{ui} and @{i}Quick@{ui}.

   @{b}*@{ub} Added new menu item @{i}Mark & Delete@{ui} for multiple thumbnail removal.

   @{b}*@{ub} Changed (Improved?) most of the screen displaying routines.

   @{b}*@{ub} The image information window now shows the path of the file too.


@EndNode

